hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a function $f$ defined on the closed interval $[0, \pi]$ which assigns values based on whether a point is a rational multiple of $\pi$. Specifically, the function is defined as:
$$
f(x) = \begin{cases}
\sin(x) - \frac{1}{2}x & \text{if } \frac{x}{\pi} \text{ is an irrational number} \\
100 & \text{if } \frac{x}{\pi} \text{ is a rational number}
\end{cases}
$$
Assuming the standard Lebesgue measure on the real line, calculate the essential supremum of the function $f$ on the interval $[0, \pi]$. Express your answer as a single closed-form analytic expression.
